### FINDINGS
| Sub-feature | gem-team mechanism (file:line) | spec-kit equivalent or GAP (file:line) | Verdict | Effort(S/M/L) | Net-new value |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Run-learning → skill extraction trigger | Auto-Skills extract reusable `SKILL.md` files from successful tasks; skills are high-confidence pattern artifacts [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/README.md:79], [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/README.md:124] | GAP vs `/create`: our skill creation activates when user requests/scaffolds component creation, not from accumulated run learnings [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:75], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:83] | ADAPT | M | Net-new trigger source; adapt as recommendation/candidate generation, not direct canonical writes. |
| Orchestrator enrich auto-promotion | During Enrich, Gem Team promotes signals and creates skills for patterns confidence ≥0.90 via `gem-skill-creator` [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:131] | Our deep-improvement equivalent is proposal-first and promotes only after scoring, benchmark, repeatability, boundary, and approval gates pass [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:278], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:279] | ADAPT | L | High value if converted into packet-local proposed skill candidates plus approval gate. |
| Threshold + recurrence gate | `gem-skill-creator` requires reuse ≥2× and HIGH ≥0.95 to create; MEDIUM/LOW skip [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:44], [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:49] | Partial equivalent: `/create:skill` has DQI/validation gates and similar-skill discovery, but no run-learning confidence gate [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/create/skill.md:382], [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/create/skill.md:392] | ADAPT | M | Net-new eligibility policy; useful if backed by our evaluator and telemetry. |
| Direct automatic canonical skill creation | Gem Team creates `docs/skills/{name}/SKILL.md` and resource folders once viable [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:55], [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:58] | REJECT equivalent: our deep-improvement rules forbid canonical mutation in proposal-only mode and reject non-canonical promotion even if benchmarks pass [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:510], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:515] | REJECT | M | Keep safety boundary; auto-create should stop at candidate artifact plus approval. |
| Minimal skill packaging format | Gem Team generates compact `SKILL.md` metadata with confidence/source/usages and keeps content <500 tokens [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:58], [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:123] | REJECT equivalent: sk-doc already enforces richer required sections, progressive disclosure, package validation, and resource templates [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:58], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/skill_creation.md:68] | REJECT | S | No need to import weaker format; preserve sk-doc template/validation. |

- [F-007-01] Gem Team’s net-new part is automatic harvesting from successful-task learnings into skill candidates; spec-kit currently has user/request-driven `/create` skill creation and a six-step manual/evaluator workflow instead [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/README.md:79], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md:83].
- [F-007-02] The confidence/recurrence thresholds are worth adapting, but Gem Team’s thresholds conflict with our evaluator-first model unless converted into evidence inputs for candidate scoring [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:45], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:243].
- [F-007-03] Direct auto-creation of canonical skills should be rejected because our equivalent intentionally separates packet-local candidates from guarded promotion [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:57], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:236].
- [F-007-04] Best adoption path: auto-detect recurring high-confidence patterns, generate a packet-local `/create:sk-skill` pre-bound candidate, run sk-doc validation, then require human/operator promotion [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:131], [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/create/assets/create_sk_skill_auto.yaml:347].

### NEGATIVE / RULED-OUT
- Rule out automatic canonical `SKILL.md` creation during normal enrich. It bypasses our proposal-first and approval-gated mutation boundary [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-orchestrator.agent.md:131], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md:278].
- Rule out importing Gem Team’s compact skill format. Our sk-doc skill anatomy and validation requirements are more complete and already productionized [SOURCE: specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/gem-team-main/.apm/agents/gem-skill-creator.agent.md:123], [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:112].

### OPEN QUESTIONS
- Should pattern frequency/confidence be sourced from memory, spec packets, deep-improvement journals, or skill-benchmark telemetry?
- Should auto-extraction create only a `/create:sk-skill` pre-bound config, or also draft a packet-local candidate skill folder?
- What approval threshold should promote a candidate skill: DQI only, skill-benchmark pass, deep-improvement score, or all three?

